{"tid":1912711,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"ha 今日派垃圾口罩俾d 後勤用，仲send d 咁既文俾後勤","createTime":"2020-03-06T09:16:37.000Z","updateTime":"2020-03-06T16:27:38.000Z","uid":38962,"like":7,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":15,"replies":[{"pid":"4b752d10dad69a71a915f04cf636e28df764bb33","tid":1912711,"uid":38962,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-06T09:16:37.000Z","msg":"Dear Colleagues,<br />\n<br />\nHO Admin has been facilitating the provision of facemasks to Head Office colleagues for prudent and reasonable use in their work operation.  Due to the outbreak situation particularly recently in different places of the world, the supply of surgical masks (as well as other PPEs) locally and worldwide remains tight and uncertain, and as emphasised, priority is for clinical use. <br />\n<br />\nDespite the challenges, we shall continue to strive to provide facemasks to support staff in work under permitting circumstance and where practicable.  For the provision for next week and onwards, facemasks of different styles will be distributed including of different colours, ear-loop, tie-on, better fit for lean-faced etc.   Like many facemasks commercially available in the market, they have infection control functions and are considered appropriate for non-clinical use, while they do not meet the full range of stringent standard requirements for surgical masks for clinical use, which for example, include specific level of fluid penetration resistance in addition to various standards on Bacterial Filtration Efficiency, and Sub-micron Particulate Filtration Efficiency etc.  <br />\n<br />\nColleagues may wish to know that through optimizing the deployment, we are relieving surgical masks back to the frontline for clinical use.  Let&rsquo;s join hands to fight the virus. <br />\n<br />\nThank you for your attention. <br />\n<br />\n<br />\nAdministration Department<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n笑撚死，唔撚夠就唔好要人返office啦"},{"pid":"97da8826a2949f48f0ff6c9c3ea25b0fd47cb556","t